<body>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:0px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:91.34px" class="cls_003"><span class="cls_003">B2B SEO Part 1 - Understanding the Basics</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:134.30px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">B2B SEO is one of the most effective and proven techniques to draw more customers and grow</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:148.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">your business revenue. However, many B2B companies these days give up on SEO too soon</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:163.46px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">because they feel it’s highly competitive and time consuming. Well, none of that is true. There</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:177.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">are several misconceptions and myths about B2B SEO, particularly surrounding the purpose</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:192.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">and technicalities. Therefore, it’s important for B2B companies to understand the basics of SEO.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:225.14px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">B2B SEO - An Overview</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:263.81px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">SEO stands for search engine optimization. It’s basically a method of getting your website (web</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:278.45px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">pages) to show up in search engine results.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:307.49px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">SEO is not at all a secret method to tweak the search engine’s algorithm to boost your ranking.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:322.01px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">B2B SEO comprises a variety of optimizations (content, site structure, images, internal links,</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:336.65px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">external links, and so on) to align your website better with the search engine’s standards. After</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:351.17px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">all, the mission of search engines, such as Google is organizing the world’s information and</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:365.69px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">making it universally accessible and useful.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:394.73px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Therefore, the more accessible and useful your </span><A HREF="https://blog.ccmarketing-communications.com/how-to-choose-the-right-b2b-landing-page-tools">B2B website</A> </span><span class="cls_002"> and content, the better will be your</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:409.39px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">search engine ranking.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:442.03px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">Types of B2B SEO</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:480.67px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">There are three types of B2B SEO techniques that can be used to improve the search engine</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:495.19px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">page rank (SERP) of your B2B company. These include:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:524.35px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   On-page SEO</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:538.87px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Off-page SEO</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:553.39px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   Technical SEO</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:582.58px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Let’s look at each in a little more detail.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:611.62px" class="cls_008"><span class="cls_008">On-Page SEO</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:640.78px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">On-page SEO is a collection of all factors that help in making a particular page rank. The most</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:655.30px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">critical factor of on-page SEO is your “content.” Therefore, it is also known as “content SEO.”</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:669.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">So, when you are talking about top-ranking keywords, headlines, meta-titles, meta-descriptions,</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:684.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">readability, engagement, and so on, you are talking about on-page SEO.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:698.86px" class="cls_008"><span class="cls_008">Off-Page SEO</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:802px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:85.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Off-page SEO is everything that doesn’t happen directly on your web page. Off-page SEO is</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:100.34px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">more about </span><A HREF="https://blog.ccmarketing-communications.com/effective-b2b-link-building-strategies">link building</A> </span><span class="cls_002"> (backlinks from other sites), social media and other promotional</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:114.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">methods, beyond your web page content and design, to help your web page rank higher in the</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:129.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">search results.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:158.54px" class="cls_008"><span class="cls_008">Technical SEO</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:187.70px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Technical SEO involves technical aspects of your web page, such as a mobile-friendly website,</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:202.22px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">SSL certificates, your website structure, and so on.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:231.26px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">However, B2B SEO can get somewhat confusing at time with different types of SEO</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:245.93px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">overlapping. For example, the time taken by a web page to load can affect the search engine</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:260.45px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">ranking of your website - that’s both on-page and technical SEO.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:293.09px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">How are B2B and B2C SEO Different?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:331.73px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">There’s a world of difference between B2B and B2C SEO. Even though the same basic</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:346.37px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">principle, i.e., reaching your target audience via a search engine, applies to both, B2B SEO is</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:360.89px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">more about reaching multiple decision makers. For example, if your B2B SaaS company is</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:375.41px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">selling an online reputation management (ORM) tool, your target audience will include:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:404.45px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   A CMO searching for an ORM software</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:419.11px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   An ORM manager searching for keywords related to online reputation</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:433.63px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">●   An startup founder looking for ORM tools</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:462.67px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Not only this but B2B SEO relies on low-volume keywords as opposed to high-volume keywords</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:477.31px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">used in B2C SEO. Every month, there are over 50,000 searches for “water heaters” but only</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:491.83px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">about 15-20 for an “HVAC automation system.” Therefore, a B2B SEO strategy should account</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:506.35px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">for low-volume, high-value keywords.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:535.39px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Lastly, B2B SEO stresses the importance of branding and thought leadership. Since B2B</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:550.03px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">search engine audiences are less likely to convert immediately, you need to establish your B2B</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:564.55px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">brand in your audiences’ memory to compel them to buy your products/services.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:597.22px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">How to Get Started With a B2B SEO Strategy?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:635.86px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Now that you know the basics of B2B SEO, it’s time you must start thinking about building an</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:650.50px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">effective B2B SEO strategy.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:679.54px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">We’ll help you with a quick step-by-step SEO guide for your B2B company.</span></div>
</div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:50%;margin-left:-306px;top:1604px;width:612px;height:792px;border-style:outset;overflow:hidden">
<div style="position:absolute;left:0px;top:0px">
<img src="{{ asset('img/background6.jpg')}}" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:71.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">First things first, there’s no chance SEO will get over complicated if you keep it simple.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:85.82px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Therefore, start simple and focus on one thing at a time.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:114.98px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">B2B SEO revolves around three key questions:</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:144.02px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">1.  What are your audiences looking for?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:158.54px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">2.  How will you provide them with what they are looking for?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:90.02px;top:173.18px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">3.  How will you convince search engines that you are providing your audiences with what</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.02px;top:187.70px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">they are looking for?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:216.74px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">We’ll cover B2B SEO best practices and strategies in Part 2 of the B2B SEO series. Stay tuned</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.02px;top:231.26px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">for more information.</span></div>
</div>

